# All Possible Interview Questions With Answers

---

## Category 1 — Basic Project Questions

---

**Q1. Tell me about your project.**

> "I built an Item Management System for an e-commerce platform using Spring Boot microservices. It has 4 independent services — Item Service, Inventory Service, Notification Service, and Audit Service. Each service runs on its own port, has its own MySQL database, and handles one specific job. All APIs are secured with JWT authentication and documented with Swagger."

---

**Q2. Why did you choose microservices over a monolithic application?**

> "In a monolithic application everything is in one place. If one part breaks, the whole application goes down. With microservices, each service is independent. If the Notification Service goes down, Item Service and Inventory Service keep running perfectly. Also each service can be scaled independently based on load."

---

**Q3. How many services did you build and what does each do?**

> - Item Service — manages product catalog, CRUD operations on items
> - Inventory Service — tracks stock levels, warehouse locations, low stock alerts
> - Notification Service — logs and manages notifications sent for events
> - Audit Service — records every important operation for tracking and compliance

---

**Q4. Which technologies did you use?**

> - Java 17
> - Spring Boot 3.2
> - Spring Data JPA and Hibernate
> - Spring Security
> - MySQL database
> - JWT for authentication
> - Swagger / SpringDoc OpenAPI for documentation
> - Lombok to reduce boilerplate code
> - JUnit and Mockito for testing
> - Maven for build management

---

**Q5. What is the port number of each service?**

> - Item Service → 8081
> - Inventory Service → 8082
> - Notification Service → 8083
> - Audit Service → 8084

---

**Q6. What databases did you use?**

> MySQL with 4 separate databases:
> - item_db for Item Service
> - inventory_db for Inventory Service
> - notification_db for Notification Service
> - audit_db for Audit Service

